phpMyAdmin - Readme
===================

Install

- git clone git@github.com:hbt/phpmyadmin.git
- install apache + php + mysql 
- configure mysql user: root , password: password
- copy examples/phpmyadmin-apache-config to /etc/apache2/sites-enabled
- create phpmyadmin database
- load example/create_tables.sql
- clear all cookies




Features and scripts:

- Clean UI + simple listing with no extra frames
- build relations using script instead of using "relation view" to display linkable foreign keys in myisam engine custom-scripts/build-relations.php
- quick lookup without having to access search field
- well configured for local use



*Reverted to phpmyadmin3 because ajax / history navigation is not well implemented in phpmyadmin4*
